cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.DS 

This paper deals with path planning for a robot on a graph with edge costs and Boolean success/failure probabilities, which is a problem commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence and robotics (cs.AI, cs.RO). The proposed solution involves a game-theoretic framework, which falls under the category of computational game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper formulates the problem as a Markov Decision Process, which is a common technique in control theory and systems engineering (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes fast and non-myopic path planners, which could fall under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
